refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     8.0.0

      hash_hmac now throws a ValueError
      exception if algo is unknown or is a
      non-cryptographic hash function; previously, &false; was returned instead.




     7.2.0
     Usage of non-cryptographic hash functions (adler32, crc32, crc32b, fnv132, fnv1a32, fnv164, fnv1a64, joaat) was disabled.

  &reftitle.examples;



    hash_hmac example


<?php
echo hash_hmac('ripemd160', 'The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog.', 'secret');
?>


    &example.outputs;


